# Cachy-Void scheduled-update service configuration — architecture.md §4.9.
# Sourced by /etc/sv/cachy-void-update/run. Rendered by deploy.sh (@USER@/@ENGINE@).
#
# This service is OPT-IN: deploy.sh installs it but only enables it when you pass
# --with-schedule (or symlink it into /var/service yourself). When enabled it
# runs `--sync` then `--commit --yes` unattended at the configured daily time.
#
# CACHY_USER    — unprivileged updater user (holds the §4 sudoers grants).
# CACHY_ENGINE  — install dir of the mirrored engine (cachy_void_update.py + engine/).
# CACHY_CONFIG  — path to updater.toml.
# SNOOZE_HOUR   — hour-of-day for the run (0-23), snooze -H field.
# SNOOZE_MINUTE — minute-of-hour for the run (0-59), snooze -M field.
#                 Both accept snooze patterns for finer control, e.g.
#                 SNOOZE_HOUR="*/6" (every 6 hours) or SNOOZE_MINUTE="0,30".
CACHY_USER=@USER@
CACHY_ENGINE=@ENGINE@
CACHY_CONFIG=/etc/cachy-void/updater.toml
SNOOZE_HOUR=5
SNOOZE_MINUTE=30
